---
/**
 * Studio About Page
 * Explains the method and purpose
 */
import StudioLayout from '../../studio/StudioLayout.astro';
---

<StudioLayout title="About Studio" palette="noir" motion="subtle">
  <article class="about">
    <header class="about-header">
      <h1 class="about-title">About Studio</h1>
      <p class="about-subtitle">On method and purpose</p>
    </header>

    <div class="about-content studio-prose">
      <section>
        <h2>What This Is</h2>
        <p>
          Everything here serves the idea. Form, motion, and type exist only to make thought clear.
        </p>
        <p>
          Notes stay in the margin. Footnotes open in place. Pull quotes bring the core into view.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Writing for Studio</h2>
        <p>
          Essays are conceptual rather than personal. They build ideas through argument and illustration. The writing is clear, the structure deliberate, each sentence necessary.
        </p>
        <p>
          Topics may move between design, philosophy, and technical systems. The common thread is precision and visual clarity.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Interaction Vocabulary</h2>
        <p>Studio essays use a small set of simple, focused components:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>MarginNote</strong>: shows side notes in the margin on desktop, inline on mobile. Good for quick asides.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Footnote</strong>: expands inline on click. Adds context without sending the reader away.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>PullQuote</strong>: surfaces a key line. Align left, center, or right; normal or large size.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>DefinitionPopover</strong>: click a term to see a short definition. Places itself to the side when there is room, or below on smaller screens. Closes on outside click or Escape. A small caret points back to the term.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>ClaimCounter</strong>: two buttons that toggle between a claim and a counterexample. Keeps the comparison tight.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>DialecticTabs</strong>: three tabs for thesis, antithesis, and synthesis. Arrow keys move between them.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>AudioPlayer</strong>: optional and off by default. Sits at the bottom right. Play or pause with one click. A volume slider lets you set the level.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Accessibility and motion</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Tabs are keyboard accessible; Left and Right switch between them.</li>
          <li>Popovers and footnotes close on Escape and outside click.</li>
          <li>Focus styles are visible and consistent.</li>
          <li>Prefers reduced motion is respected; animations calm down when requested.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>On Separation</h2>
        <p>
          Studio is separate from the main site. It has its own layout, design system, and aesthetic. The only connection is a small link in the footer.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Get in Touch</h2>
        <p>
          Questions, suggestions, or critiques? Find me on the
          <a href="/" rel="home">main site</a>. Studio is an ongoing experiment. It will evolve as I learn what works.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>

    <footer class="about-footer">
      <div class="about-back">
        <a href="/studio" class="about-back-link" aria-label="Back to Studio essays">‚Üê Back to essays</a>
      </div>
    </footer>
  </article>

  <style>
    .about {
      max-width: 720px;
      margin: 0 auto;
    }

    .about-header {
      margin-bottom: var(--studio-space-16);
      padding-bottom: var(--studio-space-8);
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--studio-border);
      opacity: 0;
      animation: fadeIn var(--studio-duration-slow) var(--studio-ease-out) forwards;
    }

    @keyframes fadeIn {
      from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(20px); }
      to { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
    }

    .about-title {
      font-family: var(--studio-font-sans);
      font-size: var(--studio-text-4xl);
      font-weight: 600;
      letter-spacing: var(--studio-tracking-tight);
      line-height: var(--studio-leading-tight);
      color: var(--studio-text-primary);
      margin-bottom: var(--studio-space-4);
    }

    .about-subtitle {
      font-size: var(--studio-text-xl);
      color: var(--studio-text-muted);
      font-style: italic;
    }

    .about-content {
      opacity: 0;
      animation: fadeIn var(--studio-duration-slow) var(--studio-ease-out) 0.2s forwards;
    }

    .about-content section {
      margin-bottom: var(--studio-space-16);
    }

    .about-content section:last-of-type {
      margin-bottom: var(--studio-space-12);
    }

    .about-footer {
      margin-top: var(--studio-space-16);
      padding-top: var(--studio-space-8);
      border-top: 1px solid var(--studio-border);
    }

    .about-back-link {
      font-family: var(--studio-font-sans);
      font-size: var(--studio-text-sm);
      color: var(--studio-text-muted);
      text-decoration: none;
      letter-spacing: var(--studio-tracking-wide);
      transition: color var(--studio-duration-normal) var(--studio-ease-out);
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: var(--studio-space-2);
      border: none;
    }

    .about-back-link:hover {
      color: var(--studio-text-primary);
    }

    @media (max-width: 768px) {
      .about-title { font-size: var(--studio-text-3xl); }
      .about-subtitle { font-size: var(--studio-text-lg); }
    }

    @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
      .about-header, .about-content { animation: none; opacity: 1; }
    }
  </style>
</StudioLayout>
